Abstract = {{We study the many-body dynamics of stimulated Raman adiabatic passage in
   the presence of on-site interactions. In the classical mean-field limit,
   explored in A. Dey et al. {[}Phys. Rev. Len. 121, 250405 (2018)],
   interaction-induced chaos leads to the breakdown of adiabaticity under
   the quasistatic variation of the parameters, thus producing
   low-sweep-rate boundaries on efficient population transfer. We show that
   for the corresponding many-body system, alternative quantum pathways
   from the initial to the target state open up at even slower sweep rates.
   These quantum detours avoid the chaotic classical path and hence allow a
   robust and efficient population transfer.}},
